      "text": "2. Parking brake release"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Parking brake pedal removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "702_3.0_jpn_11581645_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Disconnect the coupler (B). Remove the cable clip (C). Remove the joint pin clip (D) and joint pin (E). Remove the parking brake cable A. Remove the parking brake pedal (F)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not forcibly twist or strongly bend the parking brake cable. A deformed or damaged cable may cause malfunction or cut damage."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Parking brake switch removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "702_3.0_jpn_11581646_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the parking brake switch (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "702_3.0_jpn_11581647_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure. Clip (A) is installed as shown in the figure."
